%% DentiVerse — Payment & Escrow Flow
%% Shows how money moves through the system from client to designer.

sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant DV as DentiVerse API
    participant S as Stripe Connect
    participant D as Designer

    C->>DV: Accept proposal ($85)
    DV->>S: Create PaymentIntent ($85)
    S-->>DV: client_secret
    DV-->>C: Show payment form

    C->>S: Confirm payment (card)
    S-->>DV: Webhook: payment_intent.succeeded
    DV->>DV: Create Payment (status: HELD)
    DV->>DV: Update case (status: ASSIGNED)
    DV-->>D: Notification: "Case assigned"

    Note over D: Designer works on design...

    D->>DV: Upload design files
    DV->>DV: Update case (status: REVIEW)
    DV-->>C: Notification: "Design ready"

    C->>DV: Approve design
    DV->>DV: Update case (status: COMPLETED)
    DV->>S: Create Transfer ($85 - 12% fee = $74.80)
    S-->>D: Payout to designer bank
    DV->>DV: Update Payment (status: RELEASED)
    DV-->>C: Design files downloadable
    DV-->>D: Notification: "Payment released"
